00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
[Intro music]

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.230
The paysanne cut is not a very

00:00:10.230 --> 00:00:12.120
sophisticated cut.

00:00:12.120 --> 00:00:15.210
Depending on the vegetable, the shape of

00:00:15.210 --> 00:00:18.250
the cut can be either square, triangle,

00:00:18.250 --> 00:00:21.060
half-moon shape, circle and so on.

00:00:21.060 --> 00:00:25.210
So the idea really is to have everything small,

00:00:25.210 --> 00:00:28.140
up to 2 millimeters for the rectangle

00:00:28.140 --> 00:00:31.180
or for long shapes, and it can be square

00:00:31.180 --> 00:00:32.260
up to a centimeter.

00:00:32.260 --> 00:00:36.080
Now the idea really is to have everything

00:00:36.080 --> 00:00:39.060
fitting a tablespoon when you eat your soup.

00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:42.280
So here I have different types of vegetable cuts.

00:00:42.280 --> 00:00:43.210
Let's have a look.

00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:46.190
Green beans, so they're cut into circles.

00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:50.100
Celery, triangles and squares.

00:00:50.100 --> 00:00:52.100
Same thing for the carrots.

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:56.100
Green cabbage, long rectangles.

00:00:56.100 --> 00:01:00.010
Leeks, same thing.

00:01:00.010 --> 00:01:04.130
Square of turnips, with a few triangles.

00:01:04.130 --> 00:01:06.100
And potatoes, same shape.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.070
To cut the carrots into paysanne,

00:01:16.070 --> 00:01:18.070
you want to have many small pieces.

00:01:18.070 --> 00:01:19.220
So cut them in half.

00:01:19.220 --> 00:01:22.290
Cut the thinnest part lengthwise

00:01:22.290 --> 00:01:31.000
into four pieces. [cutting sounds]

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:32.090
Then put them together.

00:01:32.090 --> 00:01:34.240
Position your finger, claw position.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:40.110
And cut it into little triangles.

00:01:40.110 --> 00:01:41.030
Cut the other part lengthwise into

00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:53.280
three pieces. Put them all together.

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:56.030
Position your hand in a claw position.

00:01:56.030 --> 00:02:04.000
And cut it. [cutting sounds]

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.040
So as you can see a paysanne can be

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:09.290
square or triangle for carrots.

00:02:09.290 --> 00:02:12.230
So repeat the operation

00:02:12.230 --> 00:02:15.000
with the remaining carrots.

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:22.250
To cut your turnips into paysanne

00:02:22.250 --> 00:02:25.040
you need to cut them into a square of

00:02:25.040 --> 00:02:28.020
5 millimeters, which is exactly the same

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:30.290
size as macedoine. Let me show you.

00:02:30.290 --> 00:02:35.140
Cut your turnips into 5 millimeter slices.

00:02:35.140 --> 00:02:49.110
[cutting sounds] Then cut your slices

00:02:49.110 --> 00:02:57.280
into 5 millimeter sticks. Rotate.

00:02:57.280 --> 00:03:01.220
Don't worry about the trimmings or the corners.

00:03:01.220 --> 00:03:06.110
Then cut each sticks into 5 millimeter squares.

00:03:06.110 --> 00:03:14.040
And repeat the operation for all the slices.

00:03:14.040 --> 00:03:19.000
[cutting sounds]

00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:25.190
To cut your leek into paysanne

00:03:25.190 --> 00:03:27.010
you will need to wash it first.

00:03:27.010 --> 00:03:29.120
And then because you have split it

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.190
in order to wash it, then you're going to

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:33.000
go through and you're going to

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:34.110
divide the larger leaves.

00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:42.020
Like this one for example or that one.

00:03:42.020 --> 00:03:53.090
[slicing sounds] And this one. Good.
